13/01/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The NATO summit hosted by Bucharest in early April will be the biggest ever, in terms of the number of delegates expected, NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer said after meeting with Romanian President Traian Basescu on Friday (January 11th) in Bucharest. 
De Hoop Scheffer said that he and Basescu discussed organisational issues and preparations, which the NATO chief says are on track. 
For his part, Basescu said Romania supports the accession of Albania, Croatia and Macedonia, and said he hopes Serbia, Bosnia and Herzegovina and Montenegro will be "brought closer" to NATO. 
(DPA, Makfax, Rompres, Mediafax, New Europe, Xinhua, Fena - 11/01/08)
